<br>
Goto: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com">EQTraders</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Quite a few of the &quot;trivials&quot; have been updated.  A good rule of thumb is take your skill, add 30 to it and look for something that trivials around that range, then make that item until it's within 4-5 points of trivial then look for another item that's 30ish points away.<br>
<br>
Ayiar<br>
<br>
PS: My personal opinion is that the easiest/best skill ups come when you are approximately 10-20 points below the trivial.  Once you are within 10 it slows down dramatically imo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utotteswede.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotteSwede</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/26/02 6:38:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good Smithing For noobs guide?</span><hr size=1> For many its better to do whatever is closest to being trivial since that will give higher success-rate, aka more money back on made items. If you don´t care about cash (or product is worthless) then it´s of no concern of course.<br>
